Pairs → use one alert per pair:
SYSTEM_HA_REDUN_GROUP_NODE_LEFT ↔ SYSTEM_HA_REDUN_GROUP_NODE_JOINED
SYSTEM_HA_REDUN_STATE_DOWN ↔ SYSTEM_HA_REDUN_STATE_UP (you’ve seen UP in logs)
SYSTEM_CFGSYNC_DOWN ↔ SYSTEM_CFGSYNC_UP
SYSTEM_LINK_ADB_HELLO_PROTOCOL_DOWN ↔ SYSTEM_LINK_ADB_HELLO_PROTOCOL_UP
SYSTEM_LINK_ADB_LINK_DOWN ↔ SYSTEM_LINK_ADB_LINK_UP
SYSTEM_LINK_ETH_LINK_DOWN ↔ SYSTEM_LINK_ETH_LINK_UP
VPN_BRIDGING_LINK_DOWN ↔ VPN_BRIDGING_LINK_UP
SYSTEM_SERVICE_LISTEN_PORT_DISABLE ↔ SYSTEM_SERVICE_LISTEN_PORT_ENABLE (name can be ENABLE / ENABLED — confirm in your logs)
SYSTEM_SYSTEM_SHUTDOWN_INITIATED ↔ SYSTEM_SYSTEM_STARTUP_COMPLETE (lifecycle pair; usually gate with “expected up”)
